-- Foreigners Bought C$1.19 Billion of Canada Securities in March
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-05-16T12:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/foreigners-bought-c-1-19-billion-of-canada-securities-in-march.html
Foreigners were net purchasers of
Canadian securities in March led by federal  government bonds ,
the country’s statistics agency reported.  Purchases totaled C$1.19 billion ($1.17 billion) following
February’s revised net sale of C$6.28 billion, Statistics Canada
said today in Ottawa.  Foreign investors bought a net C$5.16 billion of bonds
including C$3.07 billion of federal government securities.
Non-residents also sold C$3.37 billion of money-market paper and
C$596 million of equities, according to the report.  Canadians  bought  C$3.81 billion of foreign securities in
March, roughly split between equities and bonds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
